{"parse":{"title":"Stop the War Committee","pageid":4053814,"revid":844232750,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Stop the War Committee</b> was an <a href=\"/wiki/Anti-war\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anti-war\">anti-war</a> organisation that <a href=\"/wiki/Opposition_to_the_Second_Boer_War\" title=\"Opposition to the Second Boer War\">opposed</a> the <a href=\"/wiki/Second_Boer_War\" title=\"Second Boer War\">Second Boer War</a>. It was formed by <a href=\"/wiki/William_Thomas_Stead\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"William Thomas Stead\">William Thomas Stead</a> in 1899.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Its president was <a href=\"/wiki/John_Clifford_(minister)\" title=\"John Clifford (minister)\">John Clifford</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and prominent members included <a href=\"/wiki/David_Lloyd_George\" title=\"David Lloyd George\">Lloyd George</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Keir_Hardie\" title=\"Keir Hardie\">Keir Hardie</a>. The group was generally seen as pro-<a href=\"/wiki/Boer\" title=\"Boer\">Boer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pro-boer_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pro-boer-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Against the background of political campaigning for the <a href=\"/wiki/Khaki_election\" title=\"Khaki election\">khaki election</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom_general_election,_1900\" title=\"United Kingdom general election, 1900\">1900</a>, Stop-The-War distributed millions of posters, cartoons and broadsheets, handing out leaflets to <a href=\"/wiki/Commuter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Commuter\">commuters</a> on trains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pro-boer_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pro-boer-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Its resolutions were religiously-inspired and utopian in their approach. The Committee united various <a href=\"/wiki/Nonconformist\" title=\"Nonconformist\">Nonconformists</a> who held different views in relation to <a href=\"/wiki/Socialism\" title=\"Socialism\">socialism</a>. However, the high moral tone of its pronouncements failed to achieve support from the working class, and provoked stronger antagonism than the more rational approach of the <a href=\"/wiki/South_African_Conciliation_Committee\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"South African Conciliation Committee\">South African Conciliation Committee</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stop_the_War_Committee&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Anti-war\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anti-war\">Anti-war</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Opposition_to_the_Second_Boer_War\" title=\"Opposition to the Second Boer War\">Opposition to the Second Boer War</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_anti-war_organizations\" title=\"List of anti-war organizations\">List of anti-war organizations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_peace_activists\" title=\"List of peace activists\">List of peace activists</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stop_the_War_Committee&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.attackingthedevil.co.uk/worksabout/bairns.php\">Biography of W.T. Stead</a>, W.T. Stead and his \"Books for the Bairns\", Sally Wood-Lamont, Salvia Books, Edinburgh, 1987</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.spartacus.schoolnet.co.uk/REclifford.htm\">John Clifford</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20071230223817/http://www.spartacus.schoolnet.co.uk/REclifford.htm\">Archived</a> 2007-12-30 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>., in A Dictionary of Methodism in Britain and Ireland, John Vickers</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-pro-boer-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-pro-boer_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-pro-boer_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Davey, Arthur (1978). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?ei=75M6TrHZMoGl8QOQn5HgAg&amp;ct=result&amp;id=sXF0AAAAMAAJ&amp;q=Stop-the-War+Committee\"><i>The British pro-Boers, 1877-1902</i></a>. South Africa: Tafelberg. p.&#160;220. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-624-01200-X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-624-01200-X\">0-624-01200-X</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+British+pro-Boers%2C+1877-1902&amp;rft.place=South+Africa&amp;rft.pages=220&amp;rft.pub=Tafelberg&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft.isbn=0-624-01200-X&amp;rft.aulast=Davey&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fei%3D75M6TrHZMoGl8QOQn5HgAg%26ct%3Dresult%26id%3DsXF0AAAAMAAJ%26q%3DStop-the-War%2BCommittee&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AStop+the+War+Committee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Lowry, Donal (2000). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=hOrnAAAAIAAJ&amp;pg=PA174\"><i>The South African War reappraised</i></a>. Manchester University Press. p.&#160;174. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7190-5825-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7190-5825-2\">0-7190-5825-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+South+African+War+reappraised&amp;rft.pages=174&amp;rft.pub=Manchester+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=0-7190-5825-2&amp;rft.aulast=Lowry&amp;rft.aufirst=Donal&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DhOrnAAAAIAAJ%26pg%3DPA174&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AStop+the+War+Committee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Peace_movement/Anti-war_movement\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Anti-war\" title=\"Template:Anti-war\"><abbr title=\"View this template\" style=\"text-align:center;;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none; pad